\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Improved health also represents the main pathway for the hypothesised associatio
n of reduced levels of environmental bads, such as air pollution and noise,
 with increased LS.
 As noted by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "welsch:2006"

\end_inset

, this pathway does not require that individuals are conscious of the cause-effe
ct relationship between their own LS and the environmental problem.
 However, an awareness of local air pollution and its negative effects on
 human and ecosystem health may act to reduce individuals' LS levels directly
 and independently.
 Evidence for both of these effects is examined in brief below.
\end_layout

